@kangbreder I am also able to see lot of files, which are not related to your changes.
Can you please remove those and make this PR more relevant to the Swagger docs?

Also can you please squash your commits into a single commit?

@awasum doing a rebase and squash of your #670, so that we have a simple clean git history, was much less trivial than I thought... :smiley:  because of the merge commits created by GitHub when you accepted those change proposals I made, and then made further changes.

This was supposed to be it, but it's not 1000% identical to your #670, as I had to "manually" re-port some of the changes.. thought it was very close, but seems to be missing something, as 3 ITs are now failing here. :sob: I'll see if I can figure out the difference, shout if you do first. If we can't, we could always merge yours (but this would be nicer).

I'll be raising a new PR for some additional proposed related clean up from myself based off the 2nd commit on https://github.com/apache/fineract/compare/develop...vorburger:spotbugs-extra. (We can decide later if we cherry pick those on top of #670 if you go for merging that after all, or if we can figure this one out.)

> Ok, I will rebase the branch with dev. No problem

@angelboxes were you still planning to do that? Just asking. If not, would you like to close this one?

Once this doesn't have merge conflicts anymore and builds, we need to find someone who can do a functional verification. Could I suggest that you ask on the public mailing list asking who can review this for you?
